02021%2C%20Capitol%20riot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-indictment-read-charges-january-6-election-case-2023-7%5C%22%3EThe%20charges%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%20conspiracy%20to%20defraud%20the%20United%20States%2C%20conspiracy%20to%20obstruct%20an%20official%20proceeding%2C%20obstruction%20of%20and%20attempt%20to%20obstruct%20an%20official%20proceeding%2C%20and%20conspiracy%20against%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20third%20criminal%20indictment%20and%20second%20federal%20indictment%20for%20the%20former%20commander-in-chief%20and%20arose%20from%20the%20special%20counsel%20Jack%20Smith's%20sprawling%20investigation%20into%20the%20deadly%20siege.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20new%20criminal%20charges%20Trump%20is%20facing%20and%20what%20they%20mean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EConspiracy%20to%20defraud%20the%20government%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.law.cornell.edu%2Fuscode%2Ftext%2F18%2F371%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egeneral%20conspiracy%20statute%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20fairly%20broad%2C%20but%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20determined%20in%20two%2020th-century%20cases%20that%20it%20prohibits%20%26quot%3Bconspiracy%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20impairing%2C%20obstructing%20or%20defeating%26quot%3B%20a%20lawful%20government%20function%2C%20and%20interfering%20with%20or%20obstructing%20the%20government%20%26quot%3Bby%20deceit%2C%20craft%20or%20trickery%2C%20or%20at%20least%20by%20means%20that%20are%20dishonest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20secure%20a%20conviction%20on%20this%20charge%2C%20prosecutors%20would%20need%20to%20prove%20that%20Trump%20knew%20he%20lost%20the%202020%20election%20and%20still%20tried%20to%20overturn%20the%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Congress'%20January%206%20select%20committee%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjanuary-6-committee-trump-criminal-referral-doj-capitol-riot-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easked%20the%20Justice%20Department%20to%20prosecute%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20connection%20to%20the%20Capitol%20riot%2C%20it%20included%20conspiracy%20to%20defraud%20the%20US%20as%20one%20of%20the%20four%20recommended%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20almost%20a%20certainty%2C%26quot%3B%20Neama%20Rahmani%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20in%20California%20told%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bsafe%26quot%3B%20charge%20that%20can%20also%20include%20several%20co-conspirators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20January%206%20committee%20said%20in%20a%20court%20filing%20last%20year%20that%20it%20had%20evidence%20Trump%20and%20his%20allies%20%26quot%3Bentered%20into%20an%20agreement%26quot%3B%20to%20defraud%20the%20US%20by%20interfering%20with%20Congress'%20election-certification%20process%2C%20%26quot%3Bdisseminating%20false%20information%20about%20election%20fraud%2C%20and%20pressuring%20state%20officials%20to%20alter%20state%20election%20results%20and%20federal%20officials%20to%20assist%20in%20that%20effort.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20convicted%20of%20this%20charge%2C%20Trump%20could%20face%20a%20maximum%20of%205%20years%20in%20prison%2C%20Rahmani%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EObstruction%20of%20an%20official%20proceeding%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20charge%20relates%20primarily%20to%20allegations%20that%20Trump%20tried%20to%20obstruct%20Congress'%20election%20certification%20process%20by%20pressuring%20then-Vice%20President%20Mike%20Pence%20to%20reject%20the%20electors%20from%20states%20that%20Biden%20won%20and%20substitute%20fake%20slates%20of%20pro-Trump%20electors%20in%20their%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObstruction%20of%20an%20official%20proceeding%20is%20among%20the%20most%20widely%20used%20charges%20federal%20prosecutors%20have%20brought%20against%20other%20defendants%20related%20to%20the%20Capitol%20riot.%20The%20January%206%20committee%20also%20said%20last%20year%20that%20several%20judges%20%26quot%3Bconcluded%20that%20Congress's%20proceeding%20to%20count%20the%20electoral%20votes%20on%20January%206th%20was%20an%20'official%20proceeding'%20for%20purposes%20of%20this%20section%2C%20and%20each%20has%20refused%20to%20dismiss%20charges%20against%20defendants%20under%20that%20section.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20maximum%20prison%20sentence%20if%20Trump%20is%20convicted%20of%20this%20charge%20is%2020%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Rahmani%20said%20that%20if%20Trump%20is%20convicted%2C%20he%20will%20likely%20never%20see%20that%20many%20years%20behind%20bars%20because%20prosecutors%20will%20%26quot%3Bmerge%20sentences%20...%20and%20take%20the%20most%20serious%20one.%26quot%3B%20In%20this%20case%2C%20it's%20obstruction%20of%20an%20official%20proceeding.%20Plus%2C%20Rahmani%20said%2C%20the%20judge%20will%20follow%20sentencing%20guidelines%20versus%20handing%20down%20the%20max.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20sentencing%20ranges%20are%20advisory%20and%20that%20if%20Trump%20gets%20convicted%20following%20a%20trial%2C%20he'll%20likely%20be%20looking%20at%20a%20four-%20to%20five-year%20sentence.%20And%20if%20he%20strikes%20a%20plea%20deal%2C%20he%20could%20be%20sentenced%20to%20three%20to%20four%20years%2C%20Rahmani%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EConspiracy%20to%20obstruct%20an%20official%20proceeding%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20used%20the%20same%20evidence%20laid%20out%20in%20the%20first%20conspiracy%20charge%20to%20make%20its%20case%20here.%20The%20conspiracy%20to%20obstruct%20an%20official%20proceeding%20charge%20relates%20directly%20to%20the%20government's%20accusation%20that%20Trump%20conspired%20to%20obstruct%20the%20congressional%20certification%20of%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20November%202020%20win.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20charge%20carried%20a%20possible%20prison%20sentence%20of%2020%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fdc-md-va%2F2023%2F08%2F01%2Ftrump-charges-2020-election-probe%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EConspiracy%20against%20rights%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20was%20widely%20expected%20to%20be%20charged%20with%20conspiracy%20to%20defraud%20the%20US%20and%20obstruction%20of%20an%20official%20proceeding.%20But%20legal%20experts%20were%20surprised%20when%20it%20initially%20surfaced%20that%20Smith's%20office%20was%20also%20considering%20charging%20Trump%20with%20conspiracy%20against%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Reconstruction-era%20law%20was%20originally%20passed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-may-get-indicted-civil-rights-law-kkk-former-slaves-2023-7%5C%22%3Estop%20members%20of%20the%20Ku%20Klux%20Klan%20from%20terrorizing%20formerly%20enslaved%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20trying%20to%20exercise%20their%20constitutional%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20been%20applied%20more%20broadly%20in%20the%20modern%20day%2C%20and%20in%20Trump's%20case%2C%20prosecutors%20want%20to%20use%20it%20in%20alleging%20that%20the%20former%20president%20tried%20to%20tamper%20with%20the%202020%20election%20results%20in%20battleground%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20convicted%20of%20this%20charge%2C%20Trump%20could%20face%20a%20fine%20or%20prison%20time%20of%20up%20to%2010%20years%2C%20Rahmani%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERahmani%20added%20that%20while%20the%20charge%20was%20less%20expected%20compared%20to%20the%20others%2C%20%26quot%3BTrump%20was%20allegedly%20conspiring%20to%20prevent%20peoples'%20lawful%20votes%20from%20being%20counted%20with%20the%20fake%20elector%20scheme.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20why%20it%20makes%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20he%20did%20fits%20within%20the%20four%20corners%20of%20the%20statue%2C%26quot%3B%20Rahmani%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20states%20that%20if%20someone%20died%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20conspiracy%2C%20the%20defendant%20could%20face%20life%20in%20prison.%20A%20bipartisan%20Senate%20report%20fou