%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbed-bath-and-beyond-new-app-website-discounts-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20Faces%20Criminal%20Charges%20Over%20Attempts%20To%20Overturn%202020%20US%20Elections%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%C2%A0Donald%20Trump%20on%20Tuesday%20was%20hit%20with%20criminal%20charges%20for%20a%20third%20time%20in%20four%20months%20-%20this%20time%20arising%20from%20efforts%20to%20overturn%20his%202020%20U.S.%20election%20defeat%20-%20as%20he%20campaigns%20to%20regain%20the%20presidency%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20charges%20stem%20from%20Special%20Counsel%20Jack%20Smith's%20investigation%20into%20allegations%20Trump%20-%20the%20front-runner%20for%20the%202024%20Republican%20presidential%20nomination%20-%20sought%20to%20reverse%20his%20loss%20to%20Democratic%20rival%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinutes%20before%20the%20indictment%20was%20handed%20down%2C%20Trump%20posted%20on%20his%20Truth%20Social%20media%20platform%20that%20he%20had%20heard%20to%20expect%20an%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hear%20that%20Deranged%20Jack%20Smith%2C%20in%20order%20to%20interfere%20with%20the%20Presidential%20Election%20of%202024%2C%20will%20be%20putting%20out%20yet%20another%20Fake%20Indictment%20of%20your%20favorite%20President%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20have%20testified%20that%20Trump%20pressured%20them%20based%20on%20false%20claims%20of%20widespread%20voting%20fraud.%20His%20supporters%20attacked%20the%20U.S.%20Capitol%20on%20Jan.%206%2C%202021%2C%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20stop%20Congress%20from%20certifying%20Biden's%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20on%20July%2018%20said%20he%20had%20received%20a%20letter%20from%20Smith%20telling%20him%20that%20he%20was%20a%20target%20of%20the%20Jan.%206%20grand%20jury%20investigation%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20already%20had%20become%20the%20first%20former%20U.S.%20president%20to%20face%20criminal%20charges.%20He%20has%20sought%20to%20portray%20the%20prosecutions%20as%20part%20of%20a%20politically%20motivated%20witch%20hunt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20represent%20a%20second%20round%20of%20federal%20charges%20by%20Smith%2C%20who%20was%20appointed%20a%20special%20counsel%20in%20November%20by%20U.S.%20Attorney%20General%20Merrick%20Garland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20after%20a%20federal%20grand%20jury%20in%20Miami%20convened%20by%20the%20special%20counsel%20charged%20him%20in%20June%20in%20a%2037-count%20indictment%20over%20his%20unlawfully%20retention%20of%20classified%20government%20documents%20after%20leaving%20office%20in%202021%20and%20obstructing%20justice.%20Prosecutors%20accused%20him%20of%20risking%20some%20of%20the%20most%20sensitive%20U.S.%20national%20security%20secrets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20Thursday%2C%20prosecutors%20added%20three%20more%20criminal%20counts%20against%20Trump%2C%20bringing%20the%20total%20to%2040%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20ordering%20employees%20to%20delete%20security%20videos%20as%20he%20was%20under%20investigation%20for%20retaining%20the%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20charges%20brought%20against%20Trump%20emerged%20in%20March%20when%20a%20grand%20jury%20convened%20by%20Manhattan's%20district%20attorney%20indicted%20him.%20Trump%20in%20April%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20to%2034%20felony%20counts%20accusing%20him%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records%20concerning%20a%20payment%20to%20porn%20star%20Stormy%20Daniels%20to%20buy%20her%20silence%20before%20the%202016%20election%20about%20a%20sexual%20encounter%20she%20said%20she%20had%20with%20him.%20Trump%20has%20denied%20the%20encounter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%2077%2C%20leads%20a%20crowded%20field%20of%20Republican%20presidential%20candidates%20as%20he%20seeks%20a%20rematch%20with%20Biden%2C%2080%2C%20next%20year.%20Biden%20in%20April%20launched%20his%20re-election%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%20who%20served%20as%20president%20from%202017%20to%202021%2C%20has%20shown%20an%20ability%20to%20survive%20legal%20troubles%2C%20political%20controversies%20and%20personal%20behavior%20that%20might%20sink%20other%20politicians.%20Many%20Republicans%20-%20elected%20officials%20and%20voters%20-%20have%20rallied%20behind%20Trump%2C%20portraying%20the%20charges%20against%20him%20as%20selective%20prosecution%20and%20a%20Democratic%20plot%20to%20destroy%20him%20politically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStrategists%20said%20that%20while%20the%20indictments%20could%20help%20Trump%20solidify%20support%20within%20his%20base%20and%20win%20the%20Republican%20nomination%2C%20his%20ability%20to%20capitalize%20on%20them%20may%20be%20more%20limited%20in%20next%20year's%20general%20election%2C%20when%20he%20will%20have%20to%20win%20over%20more%20skeptical%20moderate%20Republicans%20and%20independents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20his%20legal%20woes%20are%20mounting.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20three%20indictments%2C%20Trump%20faces%20a%20fourth%20criminal%20investigation%20by%20a%20county%20prosecutor%20in%20Georgia%20into%20accusations%20he%20sought%20to%20undo%20his%202020%20election%20loss%20in%20that%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDocuments%20Case%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documents%20case%2C%20prosecutors%20accused%20him%20of%20mishandling%20sensitive%20classified%20documents%20about%20everything%20from%20the%20U.S.%20nuclear%20program%20to%20potential%20domestic%20vulnerabilities%20in%20the%20event%20of%20an%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Justice%20Department%20tried%20to%20get%20Trump%20to%20return%20the%20documents%2C%20the%20indictment%20alleges%2C%20he%20asked%20his%20attorneys%20if%20they%20could%20lie%20to%20the%20government%20about%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20records.%20He%20was%20accused%20of%20conspiring%20with%20his%20aide%20Walt%20Nauta%2C%20who%20is%20also%20charged%2C%20to%20move%20boxes%20containing%20documents%20around%20inside%20his%20home%20at%20the%20Mar-a-Lago%20resort%20in%20Florida%20to%20prevent%20them%20from%20being%20found.%20Nauta%20also%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20second%20employee%2C%20a%20maintenance%20worker%20at%20Mar-a-Lago%2C%20Carlos%20De%20Oliveira%2C%20was%20charged%20on%20Thursday%20with%20conspiracy%20to%20obstruct%20justice%2C%20accused%20of%20helping%20Trump%20to%20hide%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20jury%20in%20federal%20court%20in%20Manhattan%20decided%20in%20May%20in%20a%20civil%20lawsuit%20that%20Trump%20must%20pay%20%245%20million%20in%20damages%20for%20sexually%20abusing%20former%20Elle%20magazine%20columnist%20E.%20Jean%20Carroll%20in%20the%201990s%20and%20then%20defaming%20her%20by%20branding%20her%20a%20liar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20real%20estate%20company%20was%20convicted%20in%202022%20in%20Manhattan%20of%20tax%20fraud%20charges%2C%20though%20he%20personally%20was%20not%20charged%20in%20that%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpecial%20counsels%20are%20sometimes%20appointed%20to%20investigate%20politically%20sensitive%20cases%20and%20they%20do%20their%20jobs%20with%20a%20degree%20of%20independence%20from%20the%20Justice%20Department%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20being%20appointed%20by%20Garland%20to%20take%20over%20the%20two%20Trump-related%20investigations%2C%20Smith%20had%20served%20as%20the%20chief%20prosecutor%20for%20the%20special%20court%20in%20The%20Hague%2C%20tasked%20with%20prosecuting%20war%20crimes%20in%20Kosovo%2C%20oversaw%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20public%20integrity%20section%20and%20worked%20as%20a%20federal%20and%20state%20prosecutor%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECapitol%20Attack%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Jan.%206%2C%202021%2C%20rampage%20at%20the%20Capitol%2C%20Trump's%20supporters%20used%20a%20variety%20of%20weapons%20including%20chemical%20sprays%20and%20riot%20shields%20to%20attack%20police%20and%20infiltrate%20the%20building%2C%20forcing%20lawmakers%20to%20flee%20for%20their%20lives.%20Five%20people%20died%20during%20and%20shortly%20after%20the%20chaos%2C%20while%20about%20140%20police%20officers%20were%20injured.%20Before%20the%20attack%20Trump%20told%20supporters%20in%20an%20incendiary%20speech%20near%20the%20White%20House%20to%20march%20to%20the%20Capitol%20and%20%26quot%3Bfight%20like%20hell%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bstop%20the%20steal%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%201%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20charged%20with%20crimes%20arising%20from%20the%20riot%2C%20including%20some%20who%20have%20been%20convicted%20of%20seditious%20conspiracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20his%20allies%20lost%20a%20series%20of%20election-related%20lawsuits%20challenging%20the%20election%20results%20based%20on%20false%20claims%20of%20fraud.%20As%20his%20presidency%20wound%20down%2C%20Trump%20continued%20to%20push%20this%20false%20narrative%2C%20ignoring%20warnings%20from%20some%20of%20his%20White%20House%20advisers%2C%20former%20Attorney%20General%20William%20Barr%20and%20other%20officials%20that%20there%20was%20no%20evidence%20of%20widespread%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%202022%20investigative%20report%20by%20a%20Democratic-led%20U.S.%20House%20of%20Representatives%20committee%20found%20that%20Trump%20%26quot%3Bcorruptly%20pressured%26quot%3B%20former%20Vice%20President%20Mike%20Pence%20to%20refuse%20to%20count%20the%20state-by-state%20electoral%20votes%20that%20determine%20an%20election's%20outcome%20during%20a%20joint%20session%20of%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20that%20alleged%20scheme%2C%20the%20committee%20said%20Trump%20and%20several%20of%20his%20advisers%20oversaw%20a%20plot%20to%20have%20electors%20in%20pivotal%20states%20where%20Trump%20lost%20-%20such%20as%20Arizona%2C%20Georgia%2C%20Michigan%2C%20New%20Mexico%20and%20Pennsylvania%20-%20to%20submit%20fraudulent%20documentation%20to%20Congress%20and%20the%20U.S.%20National%20Archives%20and%20Records%20Administration%20that%20he%20had%20actually%20won%20those%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690928040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-04%2Ff3ni69lo_donald-trump-afp_625x300_05_April_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-faces-criminal-charges-over-attempts-to-overturn-2020-us-elections-4260855%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20on%20Tuesday%20was%20hit%20with%20criminal%20charges%20for%20a%20third%20time%20in%20four%20months%20-%20this%20time%20arising%20from%20efforts%20to%20overturn%20his%202020%20U.S.%20election%20defeat%20-%20as%20he%20campaigns%20to%20regain%20the%20presidency%20next%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-faces-criminal-charges-over-attempts-to-overturn-2020-us-elections-4260855%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-faces-criminal-charges-over-attempts-to-overturn-2020-us-elections-4260855%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-faces-criminal-charges-over-attempts-to-overturn-2020-us-elections-4260855%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fitch%20downgrades%20US%20credit%20rating%20citing%20'steady%20deterioration'%20of%20US%20governance%20amid%20frequent%20debt%20ceiling%20battles%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227292%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20United%20States%20Department%20of%20the%20Treasury%20building%20is%20seen%20in%20Washington%20D.C.%2C%20United%20States%20on%20April%2012%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6459426565a21600192faa17%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20United%20States%20Department%20of%20the%20Treasury%20building%3Cp%3ECelal%20Gunes%20%2F%20Anadolu%20Agency%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFitch%20downgraded%20the%20US's%20credit%20rating%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Bsteady%20deterioration%20in%20standards%20of%20governance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20downgrade%20comes%20two%20months%20after%20the%20latest%20debt%20ceiling%20battle%20and%20brinkmanship.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEven%20so%2C%20Republicans%20and%20Democrats%20reached%20a%20deal%20to%20suspend%20the%20debt%20limit%20until%202025.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFitch%2C%20one%20of%20the%20major%20credit%20rating%20agencies%2C%20on%20Tuesday%20announced%20that%20it%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fitchratings.com%2Fresearch%2Fsovereigns%2Ffitch-downgrades-united-states-long-term-ratings-to-aa-from-aaa-outlook-stable-01-08-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edowngraded%20the%20US'%20long-term%20rating%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dealing%20a%20potential%20blow%20to%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20economic%20stewardship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20was%20unsparing%20in%20its%20assessment%20that%20Congress%20is%20functionally%20a%20mess%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20raising%20the%20debt%20ceiling%20to%20avoid%20a%20default.%20Lawmakers%20and%20the%20White%20House%20brokered%20a%20bipartisan%20compromise%20in%20June%20that%20narrowly%20avoided%20default%2C%20but%20the%20deal%20was%20not%20enough%20to%20convince%20the%20agency%20that%20further%20calamities%20are%20not%20in%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20Fitch's%20view%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20steady%20deterioration%20in%20standards%20of%20governance%20over%20the%20last%2020%20years%2C%20including%20on%20fiscal%20and%20debt%20matters%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20June%20bipartisan%20agreement%20to%20suspend%20the%20debt%20limit%20until%20January%202025%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20agency%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20announcing%20its%20rating%20change.%20%26quot%3BThe%20repeated%20debt-limit%20political%20standoffs%20and%20last-minute%20resolutions%20have%20eroded%20confidence%20in%20fiscal%20management.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFitch%20also%20cited%20rising%20government%20deficits%20and%20ongoing%20concerns%20about%20the%20long-term%20health%20of%20programs%20like%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare%20as%20factors%20in%20the%20downgrade%20from%20the%20top-tier%20AAA%20rating%20to%20AA%2B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFitch's%20move%20echoes%20what%20S%26amp%3BP%20did%20in%202011%20when%20that%20major%20rating%20agency%20downgraded%20US%20credit%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20a%20different%20debt%20ceiling%20fight.%20It%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20if%20Fitch's%20decision%20will%20carry%20the%20same%20financial%20effects%20that%20S%26amp%3BP's%20move%20did.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETreasury%20Secretary%20Janet%20Yellen%20said%20she%20strongly%20disagreed%20with%20Fitch's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20change%20by%20Fitch%20Ratings%20announced%20today%20is%20arbitrary%20and%20based%20on%20outdated%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20pointing%20to%20indicators%20like%20near-record%20low%20unemployment%20and%20strong%20GDP%20as%20signals%20of%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20country's%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20downgrade%20comes%20after%20yet%20another%20prolonged%20battle%20over%20the%20debt%20ceiling%2C%20although%20that%20potentially%20disastrous%20default%20was%20narrowly%20avoided%20through%20a%20bipartisan%20deal.%20Democrats%20and%20Republicans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-finally-ends-debt-ceiling-danger-by-signing-bipartisan-bill-2023-6%5C%22%3Epassed%20bipartisan%20legislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20early%20June%20to%20suspend%20the%20debt%20limit%20through%202025%2C%20with%20Democrats%20acquiescing%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href