A%20loans.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThese%20efforts%20are%20meant%20to%20close%20capital%20access%20gaps%20for%20minority%20and%20rural%20small%20business%20owners.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20Administration%20is%20making%20it%20simpler%20for%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteps-building-successful-small-business-2023-4%5C%22%3Esmall%20business%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20the%20loans%20they%20need%20to%20start%20and%20grow%20their%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20a%20series%20of%20changes%2C%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20is%20simplifying%20loan%20requirements%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20financial-technology%20firms%20to%20participate.%20The%20SBA%20is%20also%20increasing%20the%20scope%20of%20nonbank%20lenders%20that%20are%20licensed%20to%20issue%20SBA%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20changes%20went%20into%20effect%20August%201%20and%20were%20launched%20to%20assist%20small%20businesses%20that%20have%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-loans-investment-other-funding-for-small-businesses-2019-11%5C%22%3Edifficulty%20securing%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20given%20many%20banks%20have%20focused%20more%20on%20larger%20commercial%20borrowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCapital%20is%20the%20catalyst%20to%20starting%20and%20growing%20small%20businesses.%20The%20changes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-sba-isabel-guzman-small-business-administrator-2021-1%5C%22%3EAdministrator%20Guzman%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20making%20to%20SBA%20small%20business%20loan%20programs%20are%20critical%20to%20addressing%20persistent%20capital%20access%20gaps%2C%20particularly%20for%20rural%20and%20minority-owned%20small%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Han%20Nguyen%2C%20SBA%20spokesman%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBy%20leveling%20the%20playing%20field%20and%20fostering%20inclusive%20opportunities%20through%20these%20actions%2C%20we%20are%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20diverse%20and%20dynamic%20small%20businesses%20and%20innovative%20startups%20to%20grow%2C%20creating%20a%20stronger%20and%20more%20resilient%20economy%20for%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESBA%20loans%2C%20typically%20made%20by%20banks%20and%20other%20financial%20institutions%2C%20help%20entrepreneurs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-and-grow-a-business-founders-advice-2023-1%5C%22%3Estart%20and%20grow%20their%20small%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Entrepreneurs%20can%20borrow%20up%20to%20%245%20million%20in%20SBA-backed%20loans.%20According%20to%20the%20SBA's%202023%20budget%20request%2C%20the%20agency%20helped%20back%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sba.gov%2Fsites%2Fsbagov%2Ffiles%2F2022-04%2FFY%25202023%2520SBA%2520Congressional%2520Budget%2520Justification-508-2022-0413%2520updated.pdf%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sba.gov%2Fsites%2Fsbagov%2Ffiles%2F2022-04%2FFY%25202023%2520SBA%2520Congressional%2520Budget%2520Justification-508-2022-0413%2520updated.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3E%2434%20billion%20in%20loans%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20SBA%20typically%20promises%20to%20cover%20between%2075%25%20to%2085%25%20of%20loan%20principals%2C%20making%20the%20loans%20less%20risky%20and%20more%20appealing%20for%20lenders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20new%20lending%20criteria%2C%20the%20SBA%20will%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAllow%20lenders%20to%20make%20SBA%20loan%20decisions%20according%20to%20their%20existing%20practices%20for%20non-SBA%20loans%2C%20such%20as%20using%20credit%20scores%2C%20revenues%2C%20and%20equity%20to%20approve%20or%20deny%20loan%20applications.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReduce%20the%20cost%20and%20complexity%20of%20smaller%20loans%20by%20providing%20more%20flexibility.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERemoving%20cumbersome%20paperwork%20for%20lenders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20changes%20will%20expand%20the%20number%20of%20creditworthy%20business%20owners%20who%20can%20access%20SBA%20loans%2C%20including%20among%20women%2C%20minority%20entrepreneurs%2C%20employees%20purchasing%20a%20portion%20of%20a%20business%20from%20its%20owner(s)%2C%20and%20startup%20small%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20SBA%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20standards%20will%20simplify%20SBA%20regulations%20and%20clarify%20how%20the%20SBA%20defines%20%26quot%3Baffiliation%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20term%20that%20has%20led%20to%20confusion%20over%20who%20qualifies%20for%20loans%2C%20by%20examining%20who%20owns%20the%20business.%20As%20part%20of%20this%2C%20the%20SBA%20will%20include%20additional%20protections%20so%20that%20loans%20are%20made%20only%20to%20small%20businesses%2C%20as%20well%20as%20remove%20some%20rules%20that%20have%20been%20considered%20burdensome%20for%20applicants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20SBA%20rules%20allow%20lenders%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sba.gov%2Fpartners%2Flenders%2F7a-loan-program%2Ftypes-7a-loans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20loans%20of%20up%20to%20%24500%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20their%20own%20standard%20credit%20policies%2C%20with%20the%20SBA%20taking%20over%20prescreening%20tasks%20including%20fraud%20checks%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fsmall-business-lending-is-about-to-change-with-simpler-requirements-8578a895%3Fst%3D9bs1aytrjwu5swh%26reflink%3Darticle_email_share%26utm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20part%20of%20this%20lender%20expansion%2C%20the%20SBA%20said%20it%20will%20enroll%20new%20nonprofit%20lenders%20through%20a%20new%20Community%20Advantage%20Small%20Business%20Lending%20Company%20license.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%20and%202022%2C%2010.5%20million%20people%20applied%20to%20start%20a%20new%20business%2C%20according%20to%20the%20SBA.%20However%2C%20certain%20demographics%20across%20the%20US%20have%20struggled%20to%20obtain%20affordable%20loans.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20bank%20branch%20closures%2C%20the%20SBA%20said%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sba.gov%2Farticle%2F2023%2F04%2F12%2Fus-small-business-administration-implements-rules-address-persistent-capital%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%201%2C600%20banking%20deserts%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20rural%20areas.%20Fewer%20very%20small%20businesses%20have%20recently%20gotten%20loans%2C%20while%20startups%20have%20historically%20been%20viewed%20as%20risky%20by%20banks.%20Additionally%2C%20Black-%20and%20Hispanic-owned%20small%20businesses%20have%20a%20harder%20time%20securing%20credit%20than%20white-owned%20small%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20a%20small%20number%20of%20banks%20and%20credit%20unions%20make%20most%20SBA%20loans%20%E2%80%94%20half%20last%20year%20were%20made%20by%20just%2020%20lenders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20changes%20have%20drawn%20criticism%20from%20some%20industry%20leaders%20and%20politicians%20for%20potentially%20increasing%20loan%20defaults%2C%20given%20an%20uptick%20in%20lenders%20could%20lead%20more%20small-business%20owners%20to%20receive%20loans%20they%20can't%20afford%20to%20repay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20nonbank%20lenders%20will%20be%20licensed%20to%20make%20SBA%20loans%20above%20%24350%2C000%2C%20which%20some%20industry%20experts%20believe%20could%20make%20riskier%20loans.%20The%20SBA%20has%20said%20the%20three%20additional%20lenders%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Bregulated%2C%20supervised%2C%20and%20examined%20by%20SBA%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20same%20oversight%20standards%20applied%20to%20today's%20successful%20and%20responsible%26quot%3B%20lenders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmall-business%20owners%20also%20may%20have%20to%20pay%20more%20for%20loans%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fsmall-business-lending-is-about-to-change-with-simpler-requirements-8578a895%3Fst%3D9bs1aytrjwu5swh%26reflink%3Darticle_email_share%26utm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20SBA%20now%20allows%20lenders%20to%20charge%20a%20flat%20fee%20of%20%242%2C500%C2%A0on%20loans%20up%20to%20%2450%2C000%2C%20higher%20than%20the%20previous%20cap%20of%203%25%20on%20loans%20of%20that%20size.%20This%20number%20rises%20to%20a%20maximum%20of%20%247%2C500%20on%20a%20%24150%2C000%20loan%2C%20a%20jump%20from%20a%20%243%2C000%20upper%20limit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20SBA%20said%20the%20new%20lending%20changes%20will%20have%20a%20significant%20effect%20on%20demographics%20that%20have%20historically%20struggled%20to%20secure%20loans%2C%20closing%20growing%20capital%20gaps%20and%20giving%20entrepreneurs%20more%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsba-loans-small-business-lending-rules-change-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690924356000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F637b90fe2c8b9a0018cbdd28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsba-loans-small-business-lending-rules-change-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20is%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20entrepreneurs%20to%20get%20loans%20to%20start%20and%20grow%20their%20businesses.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsba-loans-small-business-lending-rules-change-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Invasive%20fruit%20flies%20have%20forced%20a%2079-square-mile%20area%20of%20LA%20under%20quarantine.%20Residents%20are%20advised%20to%20not%20move%20any%20fruits%20or%20vegetables%20from%20their%20property.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22377%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22close-up%20of%20the%20fly%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c95c6e048ff200190f4c92%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22282%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Tau%20fruit%20fly%20is%20an%20invasive%20threat%20to%20California.%3Cp%3ESeveryn%20Korneyev%2FCalifornia%20Department%20of%20Food%20and%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20fruit%20fly%20invasion%20has%20led%20to%20the%20quarantine%20of%20a%2079-square-mile%20region%20of%20Los%20Angeles%20County.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EResidents%20are%20free%20to%20come%20and%20go%20under%20the%20quarantine%2C%20but%20their%20produce%20is%20not.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20the%20fly's%20invasion%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20quarantine%20in%20the%20Western%20Hemisphere.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%2079-square-mile%20area%20of%20Los%20Angeles%20County%20has%20been%20placed%20under%20quarantine%20after%20more%20than%2020%20invasive%20fruit%20flies%20were%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20isn't%20a%20quarantine%20for%20people%2C%20like%20the%20COVID%20restrictions%20we're%20all%20used%20to%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20quarantine%20of%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20only.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20California%20Department%20of%20Food%20and%20Agriculture%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdfa.ca.gov%2Fegov%2Fpress_releases%2FPress_Release.asp%3FPRnum%3D23-121%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20in%20a%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20that%20it%20detected%20more%20than%2020%20invasive%20Tau%20fruit%20flies%2C%20which%20are%20native%20to%20Asia%2C%20in%20Stevenson%20Ranch%2C%20an%20unincorporated%20area%20near%20Santa%20Clarita.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fly%20has%20been%20spotted%20in%20California%20three%20times%20since%20it%20was%20first%20detected%20in%202016%2C%20but%20was%20successfully%20eradicated%20each%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdfa.ca.gov%2Fplant%2FPDEP%2Ftarget_pest_disease_profiles%2Ftau_ff_profile.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20CDFA%20says%20on%20its%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20time%20the%20fly's%20invasion%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20quarantine%20in%20the%20Western%20Hemisphere%2C%20according%20to%20the%20CDFA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20the%20flies%20from%20spreading%2C%20people%20living%20in%20the%20quarantined%20area%20cannot%20take%20any%20fruits%20or%20vegetables%20off%20their%20property%2C%20the%20agency%20advised.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222073%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apple%20tree%20in%20an%20orchard.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c973e7cf0778001968fe46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221446%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeople%20are%20advised%20not%20to%20remove%20any%20produce%20from%20their%20property%20to%20avoid%20spreading%20the%20invasive%20Tau%20fruit%20fly.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Coletti%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20produce%2C%20however%2C%20%26quot%3Bmay%20be%20consumed%20or%20processed%20(i.e.%20juiced%2C%20frozen%2C%20cooked%2C%20or%20ground%20in%20the%20garbage%20disposal)%20at%20the%20property%20where%20they%20were%20picked%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CDFA%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BOtherwise%2C%20they%20should%20be%20disposed%20of%20by%20double-bagging%20in%20plastic%20and%20placing%20the%20bags%20in%20a%20bin%20specifically%20for%20garbage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20residents%20might%20want%20to%20think%20twice%20before%20plucking%20an%20apple%20off%20a%20tree%20and%20biting%20into%20it%20%E2%80%94%20there%20could%20be%20larvae%20living%20inside.%20The%20CDFA%20explains%20on%20its%20website%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Badult%20female%20lays%20eggs%20in%20host%20fruit%20and%20the%20larvae%20tunnel%20through%20and%20feed%20in%20this%20fruit.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CDFA%20says%20the%20fly%20is%20also%20a%20%26quot%3Bserious%26quot%3B%20pest%20for%20agriculture%20and%20natural%20resources.%20It%20can%20infect%20an%20extensive%20list%20of%20produce%2C%20including%20melon%2C%20peppers%2C%20papayas%2C%20citrus%2C%20and%20cucumber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvasive-fruit-flies-force-quarantine-of-79-miles-in-la-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690924119000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c95c6e048ff200190f4c92%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvasive-fruit-flies-force-quarantine-of-79-miles-in-la-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Tau%20fruit%20fly%2C%20native%20to%20Asia%2C%20can%20be%20destructive%20to%20agriculture%2C%20as%20larvae%20nest%20in%20and%20burrow%20through%20fruits%20and%20vegetables.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ggoodwin%40businessinsider.com%20(Grace%20Eliza%20Goodwin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvasive-fruit-flies-force-quarantine-of-79-miles-in-la-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Airbnb%20removed%203%20rental%20vans%20parked%20in%20New%20York%20City%20after%20neighbors%20complained%20of%20feces%20and%20urine%20outside%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20screenshot%20of%20the%20van%20rental%20on%20Tripadvisor.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c81710048ff200190e656e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20screenshot%20of%20a%20van%20r