ng%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20may%20be%20other%20visual%20reasons%20the%20sharks%20seem%20interested%20in%20%26quot%3Byum-yum%20yellow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPicture%20this%3A%20hundreds%20of%20men%20stranded%20at%20sea%20in%20the%20wreckage%20of%20their%20ship.%20As%20they%20cling%20to%20the%20refuge%2C%20waiting%20for%20rescue%2C%20one%20by%20one%2C%20they%20begin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsinking-of-uss-indianapolis-was-deadliest-navy-loss-at-sea-2020-7%5C%22%3Egetting%20picked%20off%20by%20sharks%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECuriously%2C%20the%20tale%20goes%2C%20every%20man%20taken%20to%20his%20watery%20grave%20had%20one%20thing%20in%20common%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20all%20wearing%20orange%20pilot%20suits.%20All%20the%20men%20dressed%20in%20green%20khaki%20suits%20were%20left%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESamuel%20Gruber%2C%20a%20shark%20biologist%2C%20recalled%20this%20anecdote%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D6oXm1-sQm8Y%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%201970s%20US%20Navy%20documentary%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20shark%20behavior.%20He%20said%20that%20story%20is%20the%20reason%20the%20Navy%20sponsored%20his%20research%20into%20shark%20vision%2C%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20determine%20why%20sharks%20seemed%20to%20be%20provoked%20by%20certain%20colors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20popular%20story%20in%20shark%20communities%20and%20is%20likely%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20myth%20that%20shark%20attacks%20may%20be%20caused%20by%20wearing%20bright%20colors%2C%20like%20yellow%20or%20orange.%20People%20even%20dubbed%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscubadiverlife.com%2Fshark-myth-yum-yum-yellow%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Byum-yum%20yellow%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESharks%20can't%20see%20color%20very%20well%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Gruber's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F3882107%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1977%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20confirmed%20sharks%20have%20sharp%20vision%2C%20it%20stopped%20short%20of%20drawing%20conclusions%20about%20color.%20But%20the%20more%20that%20modern%20research%20peers%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-white-shark-facts-2015-9%23sharks-never-close-their-eyes-except-for-the-moment-they-strike-their-prey-the-eye-socket-rolls-back-as-a-form-of-protection-during-the-attack-a-great-white-shark-never-blinks-because-it-has-no-eyelid-11%5C%22%3Eeyes%20of%20sharks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20less%20support%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20for%20the%20theory%20that%20sharks%20prefer%20to%20bite%20people%20wearing%20yellow%20or%20orange%20swimsuits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223377%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Underwater%20view%20of%20shortfin%20mako%20shark%20swimming.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c910ed048ff200190ed8c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20shortfin%20mako%20shark.%3Cp%3ERichard%20Robinson%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS1084952119301156%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2020%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20all%20the%20data%20to%20date%20said%20that%20most%20species%20of%20the%20predatory%20fish%20can't%20even%20see%20color.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20sharks%20only%20have%20one%20type%20of%20cone%2C%20which%20are%20the%20cells%20in%20eyes%20that%20pick%20up%20color.%20Most%20humans%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-it-looks-like-to-be-color-blind-2018-1%5C%22%3Ehave%20three%20types%20of%20cones%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20allows%20us%20to%20be%20sensitive%20to%20a%20whole%20range%20of%20colors%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpink-light-doesnt-really-exist-2015-8%5C%22%3Evisible%20light%20spectrum%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20because%20sharks%20only%20have%20one%20type%20of%20the%20cell%2C%20they%20can%20only%20see%20in%20shades%20of%20black%2C%20white%2C%20and%20gray%2C%20the%20review%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20this%20limited%20palette%2C%20the%20sharks%20are%20extra%20sensitive%20to%20differences%20between%20colors%20because%20their%20eyes%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.biologists.com%2Fjeb%2Farticle%2F219%2F24%2F3971%2F16519%2FVisual-resolution-and-contrast-sensitivity-in-two%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esensitive%20to%20light%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20also%20clues%20them%20in%20to%20how%20vibrant%20a%20color%20is%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.floridamuseum.ufl.edu%2Fshark-attacks%2Freduce-risk%2Fapparel-color%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Florida's%20international%20shark%20file%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20swimmers%20wearing%20bright%20colors%2C%20it's%20not%20the%20shade%20that%20sharks%20see%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bit's%20the%20contrast%20that%20they%20can%20pick%20up%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Gavin%20Naylor%2C%20director%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Florida's%20Program%20for%20Shark%20Research%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Ffuture%2Farticle%2F20230720-yum-yum-yellow-are-sharks-attracted-to-bright-colours%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESharks%20may%20be%20attracted%20by%20contrasting%20colors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENathan%20Hart%2C%20who%20authored%20the%202020%20review%2C%20stated%20that%20contrast%20may%20be%20the%20attribute%20attracting%20the%20sharks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20it%20isn't%20one%20specific%20color%20that%2