cial%20status%20of%20the%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%2C%20a%20scheme%20of%20administration%20has%20to%20be%20formulated%20by%20Parliamentary%20legislation%20to%20balance%20both%20local%20and%20national%20interests%20to%20reflect%20the%20aspiration%20of%20the%20people%20through%20the%20joint%20and%20collective%20responsibility%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20the%20Government%20of%20National%C2%A0Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20will%20replace%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fin-effective-reversal-of-sc-order-union-govt-takes-back-control-of-services-in-delhi%5C%22%3EDelhi%20Ordinance%20%3C%2Fa%3Ebrought%20on%20May%2011%2C%20overriding%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-govt-has-legislative-powers-over-services-except-police-public-order-land-sc%5C%22%3Eorder%20by%20the%20apex%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20ruled%20that%20only%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20elected%20government%20has%20authority%20over%20civil%20servants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20order%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20had%20ruled%20that%20except%20for%20issues%20linked%20to%20land%2C%20police%2C%20and%20public%20order%2C%20the%20lieutenant%20governor%20has%20%E2%80%9Cno%20independent%20decision-making%20powers%E2%80%9D%20under%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%2C%20which%20is%20in%20power%20in%20Delhi%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Funconstitutional-exercise-of-executive-fiat-aap-govt-moves-sc-against-delhi-ordinance%5C%22%3Ehas%20challenged%20the%20move%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20bring%20in%20the%20Ordinance%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Last%20month%2C%20the%20court%20referred%20the%20matter%20to%20a%20five-judge%20constitutional%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20by%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20Nityananda%20Rai%2C%20amid%20protests%20from%20opposition%20MPs%20who%20called%20the%20move%20to%20table%20the%20bill%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20MPs%20rose%20to%20oppose%20the%20move%20to%20introduce%20the%20Bill%20while%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20government%20found%20favour%20from%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcentre-ordinance-delhi-services-violates-parliamentary-federalism%5C%22%3ECentre%E2%80%99s%20Ordinance%20on%20Delhi%20Services%20Violates%20the%20Spirit%20of%20Parliamentary%20Federalism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20opposing%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20Congress%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%2C%20cited%20Rule%2072%20of%20the%20Rules%20of%20Procedure%20and%20Conduct%20of%20Business%20in%20Lok%20Sabha.%C2%A0Under%20the%20rule%2C%20the%20Speaker%20can%20permit%20brief%20statements%20from%20members%20who%20oppose%20the%20motion%20to%20introduce%20a%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChowdhury%20said%20that%20the%20bill%20infringes%20upon%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20states%20and%20violates%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Bill%20vindicates%20the%20outrageous%20infringement%20of%20this%20government%20on%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20states.%20It%20is%20designed%20for%20digging%20up%20a%20graveyard%20for%20cooperative%20federalism%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20Bill%20takes%20away%20the%20right%20of%20the%20elected%20government%20of%20Delhi%20to%20legislate%20on%20matters%20related%20to%20services%20in%20the%20Union%20territory.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20constitution%20mandates%20that%20services%20come%20under%20the%20control%20of%20states.%20This%20is%20why%20the%20Delhi%20Assembly%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20legislate%20on%20matters%20of%20services%20without%20any%20roadblocks.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChowdhury%20added%20that%20the%20attempt%20to%20bring%20in%20the%20legislation%20violates%20Article%20239AA%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20change%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20May%2011%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20239AA%20confers%20special%20status%20on%20Delhi%20following%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20S.%20Balakrishnan%20Committee.%20It%20was%20inserted%20into%20the%20Constitution%20in%201991%20by%20the%2069th%20Amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevolutionary%20Socialist%20Party%20(RSP)%20MP%2C%20N.K.%20Premachandran%2C%20also%20opposed%20the%20Bill%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20goes%20%E2%80%9Cagainst%20the%20principle%20of%20federalism%20envisaged%20by%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20members%20faced%20objections%20from%20the%20Treasury%20benches%20who%20said%20that%20the%20MPs%20should%20only%20comment%20on%20whether%20the%20House%20has%20the%20competence%20to%20introduce%20this%20Bill%20and%20not%20on%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CParliament%20is%20in%20merit%20to%20move%20this%20Bill.%20If%20they%20(the%20opposition)%20want%20to%20discuss%20(the%20Bill)%2C%20they%20can%20do%20so%20when%20the%20Bill%20is%20moved%20for%20consideration%20and%20passing%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20parliamentary%20affairs%20minister%20Pralhad%20Joshi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20India%20Majlis-e-Ittehadul%20Muslimeen%20(AIMIM)%20MP%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20said%20that%20he%20opposed%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Bill%20as%20it%20violated%20Article%20123%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20President%20some%20law-making%20powers%20including%20promulgating%20Ordinances%20when%20Parliament%20is%20in%20recess%2C%20and%20said%20that%20a%20Bill%20cannot%20be%20brought%20to%20amend%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20cannot%20use%20a%20simple%20Bill%20to%20amend%20the%20constitution%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20violates%20the%20theory%20of%20separation%20of%20powers.%20This%20House%20does%20not%20have%20the%20competence%20to%20move%20this%20bill.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOwaisi%20also%20asked%20for%20a%20division%20of%20votes%20on%20whether%20the%20Bill%20should%20be%20introduced%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrinamool%20Congress%20MP%2C%20Saugata%20Ray%2C%20also%20opposed%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9Cwell%20outside%20of%20the%20legislative%20competence%20of%20parliament%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20override%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%2C%20the%20government%20has%20brought%20this%20Bill.%20This%20is%20totally%20autocratic%20and%20abrogation%20of%20the%20legislative%20power%20of%20the%20Union%20territory%20of%20Delhi%20under%20Article%20239AA%20of%20the%20constitution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20other%20opposition%20MPs%2C%20including%20the%20deputy%20leader%20of%20the%20House%20Congress%2C%20Gaurav%20Gogoi%2C%20also%20opposed%20the%20move%20to%20introduce%20the%20bill%20along%20with%20his%20party%20colleague%20Shashi%20Tharoor%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20found%20support%20in%20the%20BJD.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJD%20MP%20Pinaki%20Misra%20said%20that%20the%20House%20is%20well%20within%20its%20rights%20to%20move%20the%20Bill.%C2%A0Misra%20said%20that%20he%20is%20surprised%20that%20legislative%20competence%20was%20being%20discussed%20in%20the%20House%20under%20Rule%2072.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20(opposition%20MPs)%20can%20vote%20against%20it%20(the%20Bill)%20but%20on%20a%20point%20of%20law%2C%20you%20cannot%20challenge%20this.%20Legislative%20competence%20is%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20the%20opposition%20MPs%E2%80%99%20objections%2C%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20Constitution%20has%20empowered%20the%20House%20to%20pass%20any%20law%20regarding%20Delhi%20and%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20objections%20are%20only%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Constitution%20has%20given%20the%20House%20the%20power%20to%20pass%20any%20law%20on%20governing%20Delhi.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20also%20clarified%20that%20the%20Parliament%20can%20bring%20any%20law%20on%20Delhi.%20All%20the%20objections%20raised%20by%20the%20opposition%20are%20therefore%20political%20and%20have%20no%20constitutional%20basis.%20I%20urge%20you%20to%20let%20me%20move%20this%20Bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20was%20then%20tabled%20amid%20sloganeering%20from%20opposition%20MPs%20after%20Birla%20allowed%20a%20voice%20vote%20on%20whether%20it%20should%20be%20introduced%20or%20not.%20The%20AAP%20called%20the%20Bill%20an%20attempt%20to%20change%20democracy%20in%20Delhi%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbabu-cracy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Bill%20changes%20democracy%20in%20the%20country%20and%20especially%20in%20Delhi%20to%20babu-cracy.%20All%20rights%20have%20been%20taken%20from%20the%20Delhi%20government%20and%20been%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20LG%20who%20is%20appointed%20by%20the%20BJP%2C%E2%80%9D%20ANI%20quoted%20AAP%20MP%20Raghav%20Chadha%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Bill%20is%20even%20more%20dangerous%20than%20the%20ordinance%20that%20it%20seeks%20to%20replace%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chadha%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChadha%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20is%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20BJP%20to%20seek%20power%20in%20Delhi%20as%20they%20have%20been%20routed%20in%20the%20last%20six%20Delhi%20elections.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20finish%20the%20government%20there%20will%20be%20no%20politics%20in%20Delhi%20and%20if%20there%20is%20no%20politics%20then%20the%20BJP%20will%20also%20not%20lose%20in%20elections.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20chief%20minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20has%20also%20met%20with%20opposition%20party%20leaders%20in%20recent%20weeks%20to%20cobble%20up%20support%20to%20block%20the%20Bill%20when%20it%20is%20brought%20to%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20INDIA%20alliance%20of%2026%20opposition%20parties%20has%20come%20together%20to%20oppose%20the%20Bill%20in%20parliament%20after%20initial%20reservations%20from%20the%20Congress%20which%20had%20remained%20non-committal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AAP%2C%20however%2C%20is%20looking%20at%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20to%20block%20the%20Bill%20where%20the%20BJP-led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20does%20not%20have%20the%20majority%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690893772000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01180657%2FUntitled-design-2023-08-01T180540.182.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Famit-shah-calls-oppositions-objections-political-as-centre-tables-delhi-services-bill-in-ls%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20called%20the%20Opposition's%20objections%20'political'%20as%20the%20Union%20government%20tabled%20the%20Delhi%20Services%20Bill%20in%20the%20lower%20house.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Famit-shah-calls-oppositions-objections-political-as-centre-tables-delhi-services-bill-in-ls%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Karan%20on%20Rocky%20Aur%20Rani%20Kii%20Prem%20Kahaani%202%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690893564000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102317823%2Cimgsize-73290.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fkaran-johar-opens-up-on-the-sequel-to-rocky-aur-rani-kii-prem-kahaani-reveals-where-they-would-stay-after-getting-married%2Farticleshow%2F102317649.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102317649.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%